            },
            "answer_text": "Everything is relative. Every object in space is still, from the point of view of its own frame of reference, and so long as it is not under any acceleration. Other objects will also appear to be still so long as there is no relative movement between them. But there is no arbitrary and absolute reference point by which everything is measured. ",
